Might I suggest the book revealing personal data about the opener  when it changes hands, so it couldn't be used to grab someone else's personal secrets directly. However, another person could persuade/compel the holder to read the contents out loud while a third person took notes. With this much potential for blackmail, no wonder the Foundation wants SCP-5134 locked away from lower-clearance personnel!








 not all surreal strangeness HAS to be evil, deadly, or even scary.






